---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ChapterNav from "../components/ChapterNav.astro";
---

<Layout title="Email Integration with Local Testing - SYP">
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-12 md:py-20">
        <a
            href="/syp-overview"
            class="mb-8 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-medium text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300"
        >
            <span class="mr-2">&larr;</span>
            Back to SYP Overview
        </a>

        <article>
            <header class="mb-12">
                <h1
                    class="mb-4 text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl text-white"
                >
                    Email Integration with Local Testing
                </h1>
                <p class="text-lg text-gray-400">
                    Async email sending with Spring Mail, HTML templates, and
                    local email testing with Papercut and Mailtrap
                </p>
            </header>

            <section class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8">
                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Overview</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                        Sending emails is a critical feature for user
                        verification, notifications, and auction results. I
                        implemented async email sending that doesn't block the
                        main request thread, HTML templates for rich email
                        formatting, and integrated testing tools (Papercut and
                        Mailtrap) to verify emails during development without
                        spamming real mailboxes.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                        Learning Journey
                    </h2>
                    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300">
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">
                                📧 Challenge: Async Email Sending
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Sending emails takes time. Can't block user
                                requests waiting for SMTP. Learned to use
                                Spring's
                                <code>@Async</code> to send emails in a background
                                thread, improving response times significantly.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">
                                🎨 Challenge: HTML Email Templates
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Plain text emails look unprofessional.
                                Implemented HTML email templates with CSS,
                                images, and proper formatting. Supports multiple
                                languages (German, English) with fallback
                                behavior.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">
                                🧪 Challenge: Testing Without Real Emails
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Can't send real emails during testing.
                                Discovered Papercut (local mail server) and
                                Mailtrap (online service) to catch emails in
                                development. Saves developer inboxes from spam.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">
                                🔐 Challenge: Secure Token Generation
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Email verification tokens must be
                                cryptographically secure. Used SecureRandom to
                                generate tokens, then store them temporarily for
                                validation.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">
                                ✅ Key Learning
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Non-blocking email sending is essential for
                                responsive APIs. Testing tools like Papercut
                                prevent real emails during development while
                                still verifying logic works.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                        Key Implementation
                    </h2>

                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">
                            Async Email Service with Spring Mail
                        </h3>
                        <div
                            class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden"
                        >
                            <pre
                                class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`// EmailServiceImpl.java
@Service
public class EmailServiceImpl implements EmailService {
    private static final Logger logger = LogManager.getLogger(EmailServiceImpl.class);
    private final JavaMailSender mailSender;
    private final String fromEmail = "info@sozialkaufhauswn.at";

    @Override
    @Async  // Sends email in background thread
    public void sendMail(String to, String subject, String body) {
        logger.info("Sending email to {}!", to);
        try {
            MimeMessage mimeMessage = mailSender.createMimeMessage();
            MimeMessageHelper helper = new MimeMessageHelper(mimeMessage, true);

            helper.setFrom(fromEmail);
            helper.setTo(to);
            helper.setSubject(subject);
            helper.setText(body, true);  // true = HTML content

            mailSender.send(mimeMessage);
            logger.info("Email sent successfully to {}", to);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            logger.warn("Failed to send email to {}! {}", to, e.getMessage());
        }
    }

    @Override
    public String generateSecureToken() {
        logger.debug("Generating secure token");
        byte[] randomBytes = new byte[32];  // 256-bit security
        new SecureRandom().nextBytes(randomBytes);
        return Base64.getUrlEncoder().withoutPadding().encodeToString(randomBytes);
    }

    @Override
    public String loadEmailHtml(String language, String fileName) {
        String primaryPath = "templates/" + fileName + language + ".html";
        String fallbackPath = "templates/" + fileName + "En.html";

        try (InputStream input = getClass().getClassLoader().getResourceAsStream(primaryPath)) {
            if (input != null) {
                return new String(input.readAllBytes(), StandardCharsets.UTF_8);
            }
        } catch (IOException e) {
            logger.warn("Error reading template: {}", primaryPath, e);
        }

        // Fallback to English
        try (InputStream fallback = getClass().getClassLoader().getResourceAsStream(fallbackPath)) {
            if (fallback != null) {
                return new String(fallback.readAllBytes(), StandardCharsets.UTF_8);
            }
        } catch (IOException e) {
            logger.error("Fallback template not found: {}", fallbackPath, e);
            throw new EmailException("Template not found");
        }
        
        return "";
    }
}`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            <code>@Async</code> tells Spring to run this in a background
                            thread. HTML templates support multiple languages with
                            fallback to English.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">
                            Spring Configuration for Email
                        </h3>
                        <div
                            class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden"
                        >
                            <pre
                                class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`# application.yaml - Development (Papercut)
spring.mail:
  host: 127.0.0.1
  port: 2525
  username:
  password:
  properties:
    mail:
      smtp:
        auth: false
        starttls:
          enable: false

---
# Production (Gmail/External SMTP)
spring.mail:
  host: smtp.gmail.com
  port: 587
  username: \${MAIL_USERNAME}  # From environment
  password: \${MAIL_PASSWORD}
  properties:
    mail:
      smtp:
        auth: true
        starttls:
          enable: true
          required: true
        connectiontimeout: 5000
        timeout: 5000
        writetimeout: 5000`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            Localhost:2525 for Papercut in dev. External SMTP
                            with authentication for production.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-3">
                            Using the Email Service
                        </h3>
                        <div
                            class="rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 overflow-hidden"
                        >
                            <pre
                                class="text-gray-300 text-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`// UserController.java - Example Usage
@PostMapping("/register")
public ApiResponse<UserDto> register(@RequestBody RegistrationRequest request) {
    UserDto user = userService.createUser(request);
    
    // Generate verification token
    String token = emailService.generateSecureToken();
    // ... store token in database ...
    
    // Load HTML template
    String emailBody = emailService.loadEmailHtml("De", "verification-email");
    // Replace placeholders
    emailBody = emailBody.replace("{userName}", user.getFirstName())
                        .replace("{verificationLink}", 
                            "https://example.com/verify?token=" + token);
    
    // Send async email (non-blocking)
    emailService.sendMail(
        user.getEmail(),
        "Account Verification - Sozialkaufhaus",
        emailBody
    );
    
    return new ApiResponse<>(200, "User registered. Check your email.", user);
}

// ItemController.java - Send bid won email
@GetMapping("/{id}")
public void processExpiredItems() {
    List<Bid> winners = bidService.getExpiredItemWinners();
    
    for (Bid bid : winners) {
        String subject = "Congratulations! You won: " + bid.getItem().getName();
        String body = emailService.loadEmailHtml("De", "bid-won-email")
            .replace("{itemName}", bid.getItem().getName())
            .replace("{finalPrice}", bid.getAmount().toString());
        
        // Async send
        emailService.sendMail(bid.getUser().getEmail(), subject, body);
    }
}`}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-2">
                            Email service is injected and called from
                            controllers. The <code>@Async</code> decorator ensures
                            the response is sent before email delivery completes.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                        Testing Strategy
                    </h2>
                    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300">
                        <div
                            class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-indigo-500/10 border border-indigo-500/30"
                        >
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-2">
                                📧 Papercut (Local Development)
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                A local mail server running on localhost:2525
                                that captures all emails sent by the
                                application. Developers can open a UI at
                                http://localhost:25 to see sent emails without
                                impacting real mailboxes.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div
                            class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-indigo-500/10 border border-indigo-500/30"
                        >
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-2">
                                📊 Mailtrap (Integration Testing)
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Online service that provides SMTP credentials.
                                Emails are captured on their servers, allowing
                                automated testing and inspection through a web
                                dashboard. Great for CI/CD pipelines.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div
                            class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-indigo-500/10 border border-indigo-500/30"
                        >
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-2">
                                🧪 Unit Testing
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Mock JavaMailSender in tests to verify email
                                generation logic without actually sending
                                emails. Verify template loading, token
                                generation, and email building.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                        Technology Stack
                    </h2>
                    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
                        {
                            [
                                "Spring Mail",
                                "@Async",
                                "JavaMailSender",
                                "MimeMessage",
                                "SecureRandom",
                                "Papercut",
                                "Mailtrap",
                            ].map((tech) => (
                                <span class="rounded-full border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/10 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-300">
                                    {tech}
                                </span>
                            ))
                        }
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
                        Results & Impact
                    </h2>
                    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Non-blocking Requests:</strong> Email sending
                                doesn't delay HTTP responses</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Professional Emails:</strong> HTML templates
                                with formatting and multilingual support</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Safe Testing:</strong> Papercut prevents
                                spam, allows inspection of all emails</span
                            >
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span
                                ><strong>Flexible Configuration:</strong> Same code
                                runs locally, in CI/CD, and in production</span
                            >
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </section>
            <ChapterNav
                prevLink="/syp-service-layer"
                prevText="Service Layer Architecture"
                nextLink="/syp-logging-strategy"
                nextText="Structured Logging"
            />
        </article>
    </main>
</Layout>
